org.netbeans.spi.java.hints

Annotation Type TriggerOptions


  • @Target(value=METHOD)
 @Retention(value=SOURCE)
public @interface TriggerOptions
    Allows to further refine TriggerTreeKind and TriggerPattern with some options. The annotation is only processed for methods annotated with TriggerTreeKind, TriggerPattern and TriggerPatterns and applies to the method invocation - applies to all method triggers.
    Since:
    1.26

      Modifier and Type Fields and Description

    • Field Detail

      • PROCESS_GUARDED

        public static final String PROCESS_GUARDED
        Causes the trigger even on code which is locked for the user. Specifically will trigger the hint on guarded block code, which the user can not modify. However some supplemental information can be collected this way by the hint.

        Hint do not act on guarded blocks by default.

    • Element Detail

      • value

        public abstract String[] value
        Options set for the trigger. See TriggerOptions constants.

        options tags.
